pr_body:
Added Okta as a provider in the existing Users and Permissions Plugin.

Main Updates -
- Added Grant config of Okta
- Added purest config of Okta to fetch user profile.

pr_body:
Signed-off-by: Hrishikesh Agarwal <hrishikeshagarwalv@gmail.com>

Updated the Auth controller to handle API request through SSO generated JWT token.

Signed-off-by: Hrishikesh Agarwal <hrishikeshagarwalv@gmail.com>

**Issue Number**

fixes #266 

<!-- Please Mention the issue number as ISSUE #(Issue Number)
Example:
fixes #1
-->

**Describe the changes you've made**

Added Okta login button on the main authentication page.


**Additional context (OPTIONAL)**

![screencapture-localhost-3000-login-1665530234143](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/54779517/195215788-f835f449-8fb5-4c34-9053-98baaedf47b4.png)


**Test plan (OPTIONAL)**

1. Set SSO to true in config.json
2. Then click on the sign-in button on the home page.
3. Check the okta login button

Updated the documentation of Okta. Added screenshots for better understanding.

Issue Number

fixes #253 

Describe the changes you've made

Added a LoginRedirect page that will handle the login callback that comes from the Strapi. Now Frontend will make a request to Strapi hosted Okta Redirect Page and not to frontend hosted. Removed previous config.

Describe if there is any unusual behavior (Any Warning) of your code(Write NA if there isn't)

NA

Signed-off-by: Hrishikesh Agarwal <hrishikeshagarwalv@gmail.com>

I have created two models-

1. User- story- permissions- In this, you can add permissions of various types like edit story, delete story , change status etc. you have to enter your name and description.

2. User-story-roles- You can add roles like manager, maintainer etc. You can add various permissions to these roles.


Now you can add these roles in the user model also.

https://www.loom.com/share/98cf092bc72c424d9e29fec8821f7584
